<br>
<br>
<br>
Overview <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Recent changes to the Skald’s Battlesong line has gone a long way in helping Skalds. Spell failure is down and damage is more consistent over the course of battles. There are still issues with the Skald class as I will outline below, but overall the changes have been positive and well received. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Concerns <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Battle Shouts – The War Howl (43) and the Battle Howl (44) seem to be reversed. The natural progression of these lines would indicate that they might have been swapped. Currently if a Skald chooses to take their weapon to 50, they are left with a secondary shout that is 2 levels below their current shout. The return for doing this as it is currently set up dissuades a possibly viable spec. <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:green;">This is just misleading. If you look at the lines in their entirety, you'll see that each new shout comes at the appropriate and balanced interval. </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
<br>
Resist Chants – Currently we have 6 separate resist chants. While it is group ability, a possible review of them would give the Skalds more to offer their group. As Skalds cannot twist their songs, only one song will ever be playing per Skald. Since that is the case, inefficient songs such as this need to be looked at. Enhancing these will also have the effect of enhancing our group abilities. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:green;">6 different resist chants is too many. This is on the list for us to address, perhaps by combining them down to 2 or 3 chants with 3 or 2 resist types. </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
<br>
Song Pulses Dropping – A long-standing issue with the Skald class is that we have frequent loss of the pulses of our songs. The speed song will drop pulses, especially when grouped, and will cause all sorts of warping effects and loss of /follow with groupmates. Our DA also skips pulses, and it is typical to see that we have lost 1 or 2 pulses during the course of a single battle. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:green;">This is a bug and an annoying one at that. Make sure it's on the bug forum so our QA folks can make sure it's in the bug tracker. </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
<br>
Defense – While the recent changes helped our Offense, and the extra HP helped our survivability a bit, we still suffer from low defense. Parry being our only means of defensive speccing does not return enough value to warrant losing offensive ability. This is probably an issue with most classes that have lower defense and the ability to spec Parry as well. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:green;">We can keep an eye on this, but skalds seem to be doing a lot better in RvR then they were before the 1.65 changes. </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Specline Issues <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Weapon – As it currently stands, the return on investment for sacrificing Battlesongs and/of Parry for higher weapon skill is poor. A Skald who specs higher in their weapon line will not offer more damage in exchange for losing offensive shouts and group chants. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:green;">There is always going to be some of this with classes like the skald. It's not necessarily designed to make it an absolutely equal return in point spent in weapon line versus a point spent in a class specialty line. With that said, what happens with the style review will likely have some sort of impact on this. </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Parry - The only speccable means of defense for the Skald is relegated to getting the leftover Spec points. A typical Skald will end up with a Parry of 17. Since we need to Spec high in Battlesongs and Weapon just to be competitive, we have to use RAs to balance out this spec. Lowering either Battlesong or Weapon does not return worthy results, even with the current changes to Parry/Block. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:green;">This is the case for many classes that choose to spend &quot;left over&quot; points in parry. Is this is just another way of talking about skald defense? </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
New Issues <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
With the addition of Trials of Atlantis, the Speed pulse-dropping bug has become even more pronounced. This also created a new issue of mobs popping into existence too late and we are on top of them by the time they are drawn to the screen. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Other Issues <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Fury of the Gods RA – Please review this unique RA since it is woefully inadequate for its cost. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Skald Epic Design – Currently it is a slightly redesigned Minstrel Epic graphic. We would like something unique to our class as other classes have. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:green;">Noted for the art team. </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=roseannelottsa>Roseanne Lottsa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Skald TL</span><br>  Posts: 440<br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/5/03 6:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=767.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skald Report Feedback</span><hr size=1> All in all, it's about what I expected.  I think the resist chant thing is hopeful, which will make them worthwhile and also give us a reason to have something else up besides DA in battle.<br>
<br>
The DD shout progression, well, I just think we have to disagree on this at this time.  We see it differently than they do, which is fine.  We can revisit this if we can better explain why it is better swapped than the way it is now.  Not a game breaker by any means so no worries there.<br>
<br>
The style review hopefully will have some impact on us.  Which as a plug, post on the other sticky all the style information and issues you have.  I need to get more in for them as soon as possible.<br>
<br>
Oh, and Yay! on the epic armor.  Maybe someday we get a new outfit and stop being the bellhop of Midgard.  At least its being sent on to the correct team to handle it.<br>
<br>
Overall, I think the feedback was positive.<br>
<br>
Rosey <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=etherag>Etherag</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/5/03 6:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=767.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skald Report Feedback</span><hr size=1> Quality Report as always Rosey.  Thanks from a long time skald<br>
