<br>
I realize the point of doing this -- to even out the flow of spell growth for skalds going from 1 to 50, and ensure that they can expect that next level of their damage shout to arrive at an appropriate level based on the monsters they fight.<br>
<br>
I think the disagreement is the focus on the part of Mythic here.  Rather than looking at the leveling growth of spell lines, more focus (in my opinion) needs to be on where those spell lines add up at 50th level.  Unless a great many other games, DAoC does not end when one reaches the final level.  In fact for many it begins there.<br>
<br>
Much of Rosey's report has an implicit point of view of issues with skalds...at 50th level (&quot;average parry of 17&quot;, disposition of spec points for BS and Parry, groups falling off a skald from the missed pulses which doesn't matter so much in the PvE game).<br>
<br>
I understand that Mythic's view as always is to attract new players, and make the leveling process entertaining even for those players making a second (or 10th) character.  I just think that given the age of the game, the class issues really do have to look at level 50 first...and all the levels up to 50 second.<br>
<br>
