<br>
I congratulate Mythic devoting 60ish people to Frontiers so they can attempt to go head to head with Worlds of Warcraft release,  but they would make a LOT of people much happier in the long  and short run if they spent some time and resources fixing the million and one no brainer bugs and ommissions that should be in the game.<br>
<br>
From a programmers point of view,  all the spells in  BS line and every other spell/style line for that matter, are just numbers in a database..  Even with horribly unorganized code, it would take 5 minutes for them to make changes to ANY global value.   if they had to recalculate the power costs manually on a spell and or change the status effects/ radius/ graphic that goes with it it might take as much as half an hour tops. <br>
<br>
with 39 classes in the game, and an excellent TL 's, if not TL program..  Just one programmer could fix a LOT the easy ommissions and nagging class specific bugs in a day or two.   <br>
